{
  "stem": "13981.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they, they attacked Stalingrad.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And von Paulus [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was-- saw what the situation was.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And being a, an army guy, a military man, he asked Hitler-- now this is his statement that I heard, myself.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He asked Hitler to surrender the troops, to save the lives.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And Hitler's response was to send him a pistol to commit suicide.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And of course, 300,000 German guys lost their lives there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But von Paulus got out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he was a very weak, old man when I saw him in court, walked on a cane, and very skinny, and very--",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Von F-- V-- you want to spell it?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "V-O-N is one word.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's the German title for the nobility.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Paulus is P-A-U-L-U-S.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was a German, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] Or was a general?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I think I-- somehow, it sticks in my mind that he was a field marshal.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, other than that they [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] fooled the guards here with that little ID deal that I told, I never met many of them, really.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They-- but the only thing I recall is-- this was the Russian media-- they wanted to take a pictures of Hoffmann.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they came in with a captain, a Russian [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] correspondent-- correspondent-- and somebody else.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they took a picture.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I happen to be in that picture.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I can say I appeared in [LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, some of it, as I said, like the evidence in Yugoslavia was actually done by the Germans themselves.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The German photographers took the pictures of the atrocities, made hundreds and hundreds of prints, and circulated them through the population to keep the population in a state of being scared.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
